It is the 46th combination in the cycle, preceded by {{ill|Boshin (Sexagenary cycle comprehensive)|ja|戊申|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Kōjutsu|ja|庚戌|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stem|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Earth (Wu Xing)|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branch|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Tori|ja|酉|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (酉)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Metal (Wu Xing)|ja|金|12=draft|12=draft}}, resulting in a {{ill|Wu Xing#Mutual generation (Xiangsheng)|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|12=draft|12=draft}} (Earth generates Metal) relationship.
== Years of Tsuchinoto-tori == Years in the {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|12=draft|12=draft}} that leave a remainder of 49 when divided by 60 correspond to the year of Tsuchinoto-tori. {| class="wikitable" |+'''Years of Tsuchinoto-tori''' |- ![[1st millennium]]!![[2nd millennium]]!![[3rd millennium]] |- | *[[49]] *[[109]] *[[169]] *[[229]] *[[289]] *[[349]] *[[409]] *[[469]] *[[529]] *[[589]] *[[649]] *[[709]] *[[769]] *[[829]] *[[889]] *[[949]] | *[[1009]] *[[1069]] *[[1129]] *[[1189]] *[[1249]] *[[1309]] *[[1369]] *[[1429]] *[[1489]] *[[1549]] *[[1609]] *[[1669]] *[[1729]] *[[1789]] *[[1849]] *[[1909]] *[[1969]] | *[[2029]] *[[2089]] *[[2149]] *[[2209]] *[[2269]] *[[2329]] *[[2389]] *[[2449]] *[[2509]] *[[2569]] *[[2629]] *[[2689]] *[[2749]] *[[2809]] *[[2869]] *[[2929]] *[[2989]] |} === Events === * The {{ill|Keichō era|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year (1609) - The {{ill|Treaty of Tsuchinoto-tori|ja|己酉約条|12=draft|12=draft}} (Keichō Treaty) was concluded.
== Month of Tsuchinoto-tori == In years where the last digit is 2 or 7 (where the {{ill|Heavenly Stem|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} is {{ill|Rin|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|12=draft|12=draft}}), the eighth month corresponds to the month of Tsuchinoto-tori. However, this may refer to the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} or the {{ill|Solar term|ja|節月|12=draft|12=draft}} (from {{ill|Hakuro (solar term)|ja|白露|12=draft|12=draft}} to the day before {{ill|Kanro|ja|寒露|12=draft|12=draft}}).
